claim.claim-text:
4. A method for preventing irregular packaging for automatic medicine packing machine that comprises a last hopper that receives a tablet discharged from a tablet cassette and contains the tablet just before the tablet is packed, wherein the last hopper comprises a shutter, the method comprises the steps of:
a) sensing whether a tablet was discharged from the tablet cassette into the last hopper and stays inside the last hopper;
b) extracting size information of the tablet that is input into the last hopper from medicine data that is stored in a controller in advance;
c) comparing the extracted size of the tablet with a reference tablet size that is preset by an operator of the automatic medicine packing machine; and
d) vibrating the shutter for a predetermined period of time if it is decided that the extracted size exceeds the reference tablet size.
